        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-802" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;1&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;The Issue: Slow &amp;amp; Inefficient Search&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;2,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;2,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Relational Failure:&lt;/b&gt; Traditional databases are too slow for &quot;fuzzy&quot; searches (e.g., searching &quot;fast cars&quot;). They can&#39;t handle complex text queries across billions of rows without lagging.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;2,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;2,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;DB Stress:&lt;/b&gt; Forcing the main database to handle both metadata updates and search queries causes system-wide performance crashes.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;3&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The Solution: Elasticsearch Offloading&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;4,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Instant Search:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;16&quot;&gt;Elasticsearch&lt;/b&gt; uses an inverted index to provide sub-second search results for titles, tags, and descriptions.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;4,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The Pipeline:&lt;/b&gt; A &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;16&quot;&gt;Logstash/CDC pipeline&lt;/b&gt; automatically syncs data from the DB to Elasticsearch.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;4,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,2,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Separation of Concerns:&lt;/b&gt; The main DB handles storage, while Elasticsearch handles search, ensuring the system remains fast as it scales.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="310" width="760" x="2450" y="3200" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-812" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;h3 data-path-to-node=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;1&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;Play Service &amp;amp; Adaptive Streaming&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;2&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The Issue: Buffering &amp;amp; High Latency&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;3,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Loading 5-10GB Files:&lt;/b&gt; It is impossible to load a full 10GB video file into the user&#39;s browser before it starts playing.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;3,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Unstable Internet:&lt;/b&gt; If a user’s internet speed drops, a fixed-resolution video (like 1080p) will start buffering, causing a &quot;loading spinner&quot; and a bad user experience.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The Solution: Adaptive Bitrate Streaming (ABR)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;5&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;5,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Video Chunking:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-5 citation-end-5&quot;&gt; The encoder creates multiple versions of every video segment (e.g., 4K, 1080p, 360p).&lt;sup class=&quot;superscript&quot;&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;5,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Dynamic Switching:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-4 citation-end-4&quot;&gt; The video player (the &quot;client&quot;) constantly checks the user&#39;s internet speed.&lt;sup class=&quot;superscript&quot;&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-3&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;5,2,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-3&quot;&gt;Smooth Playback:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;citation-3 citation-end-3&quot;&gt; If speed drops, the player automatically asks the server for a lower-quality 10-second segment instead of stopping to buffer.&lt;sup class=&quot;superscript&quot;&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5,3,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;5,3,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The Result:&lt;/b&gt; The video keeps playing without a &quot;loading spinner,&quot; even if it looks slightly blurry for a moment.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="370" width="927.5" x="2782.5" y="4680" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-875" edge="1" parent="1" source="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-876" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;" target="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-880">
