        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-1169" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;1&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 16px;&quot;&gt;The Issue: &quot;The Viral Write-Clash&quot;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;2,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;2,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Database Deadlocks:&lt;/b&gt; When millions of people &quot;Like&quot; the same viral video at once, they all try to update the exact same row in your database. This causes &quot;locking,&quot; where the DB freezes trying to handle too many simultaneous updates.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;2,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;2,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Connection Crashes:&lt;/b&gt; Your Sharded DB has a limit on how many people can talk to it at once. A sudden spike in engagement will exhaust these connections, crashing the entire service.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;3&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The Solution: Asynchronous Batching&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;4,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The Buffer:&lt;/b&gt; Instead of hitting the DB, the &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;43&quot;&gt;Engagement Service&lt;/b&gt; pushes every &quot;Like&quot; into &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;87&quot;&gt;Kafka&lt;/b&gt;. Kafka is built to handle millions of events per second without breaking a sweat.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;4,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The Worker:&lt;/b&gt; An &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;15&quot;&gt;Aggregation Worker&lt;/b&gt; sits between Kafka and the DB. It collects 5,000 &quot;Likes&quot; and turns them into &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;111&quot;&gt;one single mathematical update&lt;/b&gt; (e.g., &lt;code data-path-to-node=&quot;4,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;149&quot;&gt;Likes = Likes + 5000&lt;/code&gt;).&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;4,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,2,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Efficiency:&lt;/b&gt; This reduces the load on your Sharded DB by &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,2,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;56&quot;&gt;99%&lt;/b&gt;, keeping the system stable even during massive viral events.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="340" width="890" x="2900" y="6520" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
