        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-1272" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=center;" value="sits between Kafka and the DB" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="24" width="95" x="3685" y="8090" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-1273" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="pushes every &quot;Like&quot; into &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;87&quot;&gt;Kafka&lt;/b&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="200" x="3325" y="8108" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-1274" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;h3 data-path-to-node=&quot;1&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;1&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;1. The Final Piece: Step 5 (The CDN)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;Your system can now upload, process, and store videos. But if a user in London tries to watch a video stored in a US-based S3 bucket, it will buffer constantly.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;3,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The Issue:&lt;/b&gt; Physical distance causes &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;3,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;36&quot;&gt;Latency&lt;/b&gt;. One S3 bucket cannot handle 100 million simultaneous downloads.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;3,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The Solution:&lt;/b&gt; Add a &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;3,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;20&quot;&gt;CDN (Content Delivery Network)&lt;/b&gt; like CloudFront or Akamai. It caches your video &quot;chunks&quot; on thousands of edge servers worldwide so users download from the server closest to them.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="220" width="758.77" x="2921.23" y="8580" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
