        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-1374" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;align=center;" value="sits between Kafka and the DB" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="24" width="95" x="3705" y="10080" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-1375" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="pushes every &quot;Like&quot; into &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;87&quot;&gt;Kafka&lt;/b&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="40" width="200" x="3345" y="10098" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-1377" edge="1" parent="1" style="edgeStyle=orthogonalEdgeStyle;rounded=0;orthogonalLoop=1;jettySize=auto;html=1;">
          <mxGeometry relative="1" as="geometry">
            <mxPoint x="3127" y="9340" as="sourcePoint" />
            <mxPoint x="3175" y="9074" as="targetPoint" />
          </mxGeometry>
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-1378" parent="1" style="ellipse;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;aspect=fixed;fillColor=#60a917;fontColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#2D7600;" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 24px;&quot;&gt;CDN&lt;/font&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="115" width="115" x="3140" y="8960" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-1379" parent="1" style="text;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;2&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;The Issue: &quot;Database Hammering&quot;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;3,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Redundant Queries:&lt;/b&gt; When a video goes viral, 1 million people ask the &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;3,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;69&quot;&gt;Sharded DB Cluster&lt;/b&gt; for the same title, description, and &quot;Like&quot; count every second.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;3,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;3,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Slow Latency:&lt;/b&gt; Even with sharding, a disk-based database (SSD/HDD) takes milliseconds to respond. Multiply that by millions of users, and the DB will lag or crash.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;4&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;The Solution: In-Memory Caching (Redis)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul data-path-to-node=&quot;5&quot;&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5,0,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;5,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The &quot;Hot&quot; Store:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;5,0,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;17&quot;&gt;Redis&lt;/b&gt; stores data in RAM (Memory), which is 1,000x faster than a standard database.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5,1,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;5,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Cache-Aside Pattern:&lt;/b&gt; When a user clicks a video, the system checks Redis first. If the data is there (&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;5,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;102&quot;&gt;Cache Hit&lt;/b&gt;), it returns instantly. If not (&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;5,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;144&quot;&gt;Cache Miss&lt;/b&gt;), it fetches from the &lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;5,1,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;177&quot;&gt;Sharded DB&lt;/b&gt; once and saves it in Redis for the next person.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;5,2,0&quot;&gt;&lt;font size=&quot;3&quot;&gt;&lt;b data-path-to-node=&quot;5,2,0&quot; data-index-in-node=&quot;0&quot;&gt;Efficiency:&lt;/b&gt; This offloads 90% of the &quot;Read&quot; traffic from your expensive Shards, keeping them healthy for &quot;Writes.&quot;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="310" width="960" x="4925" y="8570" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="8HRzVfL3QyexAWrj1ium-1380" parent="1" style="image;sketch=0;aspect=fixed;html=1;points=[];align=center;fontSize=12;image=img/lib/mscae/Cache_Redis_Product.svg;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="80" width="95.25" x="4235" y="9380" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
